Powered by RubiQube Ad Network A 25-year-old male hairdresser, Akorede Adeokini, charged with theft on telephones and standing fan, was on Friday arraigned at an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. Adeokini, who resides in Papa-Ajao in Mushin area of Lagos, is facing a two-count charge of breach of peace, breaking-in and stealing. He, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. Police Prosecutor, Insp. Aondohemba Koti told the court that the defendant was caught with an iron bar, two Techno telephones and a fan at midnight by a team of policemen on patrol. He said that the defendant committed the offences on May 29 at Isolo, Lagos. “During interrogation, the defendant confessed that he broke a shop with the iron bar and stole the two phones and standing fan. “When he was ordered to take them to the shop, he refused, so he was taken to the station,” the prosecutor said. He said the offences contravened Sections 168, 287 and 406 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. Section 287 attracts three years imprisonment for stealing, while Section 406 prescribes seven years for intent to commit felony. The Magistrate, Mrs M.O Tanimola, released the defendant on bail in the sum of N80, 000, with one surety in like sum. Tanimola said that the surety should be gainfully employed and should show evidences of two years tax payment to Lagos State Government. She adjourned the case until June 24.